---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Professional bio of Carol, Senior Product Manager and Cybersecurity professional.">
  <header class="mb-20">
    <span class="section-label">Professional Profile</span>
    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-8xl font-semibold tracking-tighter leading-none mb-12">
      Systems Thinking, <br/><span class="font-serif">Trust-Centered Products.</span>
    </h1>
  </header>

  <article class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-16">
    <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-12 text-zinc-950 leading-relaxed text-xl tracking-tight">
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p>
          I’m a Product Manager with experience across Indonesian SaaS, analytics, and user adoption. Over the years, I’ve worked across growth, business intelligence, and product strategy roles at companies like Gojek and Mekari, where I focused on helping teams build products that feel intuitive, useful, and trustworthy.
        </p>

        <p>
          My recent interests revolve around digital trust, privacy-aware systems, and the relationship between user experience and security. I’m especially curious about how modern products can introduce stronger security and privacy practices without creating unnecessary friction for users.
        </p>

        <p>
          Previously at <strong>Mekari</strong>, I worked on HR and analytics products serving Indonesian businesses, contributing to product adoption initiatives, analytics workflows, and AI-assisted features tailored for local operational contexts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-950 mt-24 mb-10 tracking-tighter">Current Focus</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-12">
        <div class="group">
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-zinc-400 tracking-[0.2em] uppercase block mb-4 border-b border-zinc-100 pb-2">01 — Trust & Privacy</span>
          <p class="text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
            Exploring how product decisions influence user trust, privacy expectations, and long-term platform relationships.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="group">
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-zinc-400 tracking-[0.2em] uppercase block mb-4 border-b border-zinc-100 pb-2">02 — Security-Minded Product Design</span>
          <p class="text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
            Studying how security concepts and abuse-case thinking can be introduced earlier into product discovery and UX workflows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group">
          <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-zinc-400 tracking-[0.2em] uppercase block mb-4 border-b border-zinc-100 pb-2">03 — Growth & Ethics</span>
          <p class="text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
            Interested in the balance between analytics-driven growth and responsible data practices in modern digital products.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="space-y-16">
      <div class="bg-zinc-100 p-8 border border-zinc-200">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-zinc-400 tracking-widest uppercase block mb-6">Areas I Work In</span>
        <ul class="text-sm font-bold space-y-4 uppercase tracking-tighter text-zinc-900">
          <li>Product Strategy</li>
          <li>Analytics & Adoption</li>
          <li>Privacy UX</li>
          <li>Trust Systems</li>
          <li>Indonesian SaaS Ecosystems</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="px-8">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-zinc-400 tracking-widest uppercase block mb-6">Philosophy</span>
        <p class="text-lg text-zinc-900 italic leading-snug font-medium">
          “The best products are the ones that help users feel confident, capable, and understood.”
        </p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
